  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis of an OpenType variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes a single variation axis exposed by a variable font.
Each axis has a four-byte tag identifier (e.g., `wght` for weight), a minimum value,
a default value, a maximum value, and a flag indicating whether the axis is hidden
from UI.

Retrieve all axes for a typeface using
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters(System.Span{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis})>.

`SKFontVariationAxis` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
SKTypeface typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("VariableFont.ttf");

foreach (var axis in typeface.VariationDesignParameters)
{
    Console.WriteLine(
        $"Axis: {axis.Tag}  min={axis.Min}  default={axis.Default}  max={axis.Max}  hidden={axis.IsHidden}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
